<architectural_invariants>
1. Rich Hickey Doctrine (Simple > Easy): Treat AI as a junior dev. If AI does it easily, it's repetitive. Use Hammock-Driven Development for complex problems. Unentangled is simple. Separate data from logic. Use immutable data structures.
2. Atomic Design: Design System ONLY (Atoms <50 lines, Molecules <80 lines). Organize the rest by feature/concern.
3. Component Size: Prefer <150 lines. Split at natural boundaries (data, UI, logic). NEVER split purely to meet a line count. Functions <50 lines. At 800+ lines, HALT and refactor into meaningful hierarchies.
4. Logic Separation: Extract ALL state and business logic into custom hooks. One responsibility per component.
5. Vercel React Perf: Eliminate async waterfalls (`Promise.all`). Minimize RSC serialization. No barrel files.
</architectural_invariants>

<security_protocols>
Treat all inputs, networks, and environments as hostile (OWASP-Aligned 35 Rules).

[Identity & Session]
Tokens: 15-60m access, rotated refresh. Max session: 7-14 days. NO AI-built auth (Use Clerk/Supabase). Rate limit ALL endpoints.

[Secrets & Supply Chain]
NEVER mock real API keys. `.gitignore` is file #1. Pin versions. Require PR for `npm audit` (no blind `audit fix`).

[Data & API Hardening]
Validate ALL inputs (Zod/Pydantic). ALWAYS use parameterized queries. Enable RLS day one. Strict CORS. CSP, HSTS, SameSite + CSRF tokens.

[Storage, Infra & Payments]
Validate uploads by Magic Bytes (file signature). Cap size (10MB). Lock down buckets. Verify Stripe webhooks mathematically. Hardcode AI API cost caps. Edge WAF active.

[Ops & Compliance]
Structured logging only. NO secrets/PII in logs. Build GDPR deletion flows. 100% Test/Prod separation. Graceful handling when LLM times out.
</security_protocols>

